    <text>
        <body>
            <!-- marginal glosses on the left side of the manuscript page -->
            <ab>
                <metamark>Ø</metamark>
                <note target="#seg_Ø_1" type="commentary">
                    <p>In hac ode uelut ꝓpro sitio ẽ cuiꝰdã ĩcerti car minis. nã dubitat ꝗd
                        pͥmũ t ꝗd potissimũ di cat. utrũ cęlestiũ deoꝵ anromena. diuoꝵ &amp;
                        fortiũ ducu. om̃s tam̃ laudat cũ se fingit an cipitẽ. ꝑ.cratoriã pare
                        lepsin. uerũ meiore ĩten tume iaugusti lauder stendit. ꝙ scđm aioue. uult
                        eẽ int̃ris. Ordo÷ ó clio quẽ uirũ aut quẽ heroa sumis celebra re tibia
                        aut acrilira</p>
                </note>
                <metamark>y</metamark>
                <note target="seg_y_1" type="commentary">
                    <p> ꝓximã iouis honori mineruã. ħ ẽ uirtutẽ ⁊ sapientiã đo uicinã. unđ
                        nulla questio ÷. cum supᵃ dixerit nil iouis simile. ⁊ scđm. &amp; ĩsequenti
                        mineruã posuit. </p>
                </note>
                <metamark>∵</metamark>
                <note target="seg_∵_1" type="commentary">
                    <p>Castorẽ ⁊ pollucẽ lede filioˢ. Amatorẽ equoꝵ castorẽ dic̃. ut÷. talis
                        amrclei domitꝰ pollucis habe nis. pollucẽ uͦ pugnis ñ bellis ualentẽ. ab
                        eo ꝙ pugil fuerit. gͦ pugnos dix̃. ut t̃r. ĩuentrẽ in gere.</p>
                </note>
            </ab>
            <!-- last four lines of previous ode (carmen 1,11) with interlinear glosses -->
            <ab>
                <l>Quȩ nunc oppositis debilitat pumicibꝯ mare</l>
                <note target="#liques_1" type="synonym">bibes</note>
                <l>Tyrrenũ. sapias. uina <seg xml:id="liques_1">liques</seg> &amp; spatio breui</l>
                <note type="addition">l</note>
                <!-- target of gloss is unclear -->
                <note target="#reseces_1" type="synonym">auferes</note>
                <l>Spẽ longã <seg xml:id="reseces_1">reseces</seg>. dũ loquimur fugit inuida</l>
                <note target="Aetas_carpe_diem_quã_minimũ_credula_postero_1" type="addition">s.
                    fruere p̃serti dˢie nil crederiꝰ postero</note>
                <l><seg xml:id="Aetas_carpe_diem_quã_minimũ_credula_postero_1">Aᵉtas. carpe diem.
                        quã minimũ credula postero.</seg></l>
            </ab>
            <!-- beginning of current ode (carmen 1,12) -->
            <fw><hi>DE LAUDIBUS DEOꝵ UEL HOMINUM.</hi></fw>
            <!-- main text of ode including interlinear glosses -->
            <ab>
                <l><seg xml:id="seg_Ø_1">Ø</seg>Quem uirũ. aut heroa. lyra uel acri</l>
                <note target="#seg_sumis_1" type="addition">ꝯtendis</note>
                <note target="#seg_clyo_1" type="explanation">ó una ex uiiii musis</note>
                <l>Tibia <seg xml:id="seg_sumis_1">sumis</seg> celebrare <seg xml:id="seg_clyo_1"
                        >clyo:</seg></l>
                <note>sumis celebrare</note>
                <l>Quẽ deũ. cuius retinet iocosa nomen imago</l>
                <note target="#seg_heliconis_oris_1" type="explanation">in parnaso monte musis
                    ꝯsecrato</note>
                <l>Aut inumbrosis <seg xml:id="seg_heliconis_oris_1">heliconis oris</seg>.</l>
                <note target="#seg_aut_super_pindo_1" type="explanation">mons thracie inqͦ orpheuꝰ
                    cecinit.</note>
                <l>
                    <seg xml:id="seg_aut_super_pindo_1">Aut suꝑ pindo</seg>.<seg
                        xml:id="seg_gelidoue_in_hȩmo_1">gelidoue in hȩmo</seg>.</l>
                <note target="#seg_gelidoue_in_hȩmo_1" type="explanation">mons thessaliȩ
                    hemo.</note>
                <note target="#seg_Unde_uocalẽ_temere_in_secutę_Orphea_siluȩ_1"
                    type="explanation"> Vocales om̃s sũme uoces dnr̃.</note>
                <l>
                    <seg xml:id="seg_Unde_uocalẽ_temere_in_secutę_Orphea_siluȩ_1">Unde uocalẽ
                        temere in secutę Orphea siluȩ.</seg>
                </l>
                <note target="#seg_Arte_materna_1" type="explanation">musica scilic. nã filiꝰ
                    calliope drͣ</note>
                <l><seg xml:id="seg_Arte_materna_1">Arte materna</seg>rapidos morantẽ</l>
                <note target="#seg_lapsus_1" type="synonym">cursus</note>
                <l>Fluminũ <seg xml:id="seg_lapsus_1">lapsus</seg> celerisq. uentos</l>
                <note target="#seg_Blandũ_1" type="addition">ꝓ.de</note>
                <note target="#seg_auritas_1" type="explanation">sensũ audiendi habentes.</note>
                <note target="#seg_ducere_1" type="addition">oblectare</note>
                <l><seg xml:id="seg_Blandũ_1">Blandũ</seg>.&amp; <seg xml:id="seg_auritas_1"
                        >auritas</seg> fidibꝯ canoris <seg xml:id="seg_ducere_1">ducere</seg>
                    quercus.</l>
                <l>Quid prius. dicã solitis parentũ </l>
                <l>Laudibꝯ. qui res hominũ. ac deoꝵ. </l>
                <note target="#seg_temperat_1" type="addition">distinguit dimeeab</note>
                <l>Qui mare:&amp; terras. uarusq; <seg xml:id="seg_temperat_1">temperat</seg>
                    horis</l>
                <note target="#seg_Unde_nil_maius_generatur_ipso_1" type="addition">aqͦ ex illo qͥ
                    cuncta tẽperat. aqͥ uirg̃. unde genꝰ ducis. qͦsi dic̃ iouẽ suꝑ om̃ia sine
                    cõparatione.</note>
                <l><seg xml:id="seg_Unde_nil_maius_generatur_ipso_1">Unde nil maius generatur
                        ipso.</seg>
                </l>
                <note target="#seg_simile_1" type="addition">illi.</note>
                <l>Nec uig&amp; quicquã <seg xml:id="seg_simile_1">simile</seg>. aut secundũ.</l>
                <seg xml:id="seg_y_1">y</seg>
                <note target="#seg_Pallas_1" type="explanation">sapientia</note>
                <l>ꝓximos illi tamen occupauit <seg xml:id="seg_Pallas_1">Pallas</seg> honores.</l>
                <l>Proeliis audax neq; te silebo</l>
                <note target="#seg_Liber_1" type="synonym">bache</note>
                <note target="#seg_seuis_inimica_uirgo_1" type="explanation">dianã dic̃ studiosã
                    uenandi</note>
                <l><seg xml:id="seg_Liber_1">Liber</seg> &amp; <seg
                        xml:id="seg_seuis_inimica_uirgo_1">seuis inimica uirgo</seg></l>
                <note target="#seg_nec_te_1">s. silebo</note>
                <note target="#seg_certa_1" type="synonym">ieuitabili</note>
                <note>o</note>
                <note target="#seg_Phoebe_1" type="explanation">apolline dic̃ </note>
                <l>Beluis. <seg xml:id="seg_nec_te_metuende_1">nec te metuende</seg><seg
                        xml:id="seg_certa_1">certa</seg><seg xml:id="seg_Phoebe_1"
                    >Phoebe</seg>sagitta.</l>
                <note target="#seg_alciden_1" type="explanation">herculẽ</note>
                <l><seg xml:id="seg_tricolon_1">∵</seg>Dicã ⁊ <seg xml:id="seg_alciden_1"
                        >alciden</seg>. <seg xml:id="seg_pueros_q̨_ledȩ_1">pueros q̨
                    ledȩ̨</seg>.</l>
                <note target="#seg_pueros_q̨_ledȩ_1" type="explanation">castorẽ pollucẽ</note>
                <l>Hunc equis illũ superare pugnis</l></ab>
            <!-- new page of manuscript (folio 8r), main text of ode resumes here with interlinear glosses -->
            <pb n="8r"/>
            <ab>
                <l>Nobilẽ. quoꝵ simul alba nautis Stella refulsit.</l>
                <l>Defluit saxis agitatus humor.</l>
                <l>Concidunt uenti. fugiunt q; nubes.</l>
                <l>Et minax quia sic uoluere ponto Unda recũbit</l>
                <seg xml:id="seg_S_1">S</seg>
                <l><seg xml:id="Romulus_post">Romulũ post</seg>hos prius. an quietum</l>
                <l>Pompilii regnũ memorẽ an suꝑbos </l>
                <seg xml:id="seg_trikolon_2">∵</seg>
                <note target="#seg_Romulus_post_1" type="addition">dubito</note>
                <seg xml:id="seg_pro_1">ꝓ</seg>
                <l>Tarquinii fasces: an catonis Nobile loetum.</l>
                <seg xml:id="seg_S_2">S</seg>
                <l>Regulũ. &amp; Scauros. animȩ q; magnȩ</l>
                <seg xml:id="seg_SS_1">SS</seg>
                <l>ꝓdigum paulũ superante poeno</l>
                <seg xml:id="seg_SSS_1">SSS</seg>
                <l>Gratus insigni referã camena. Fabriciũꝙ</l>
                <seg xml:id="seg_c_1">c</seg>
                <l>Nunc &amp; incomptis curiũ capillis </l>
                <seg xml:id="seg_u_1">u</seg>
                <l>Utilẽ bello. tulit &amp; camillum </l>
                <l>Sȩua paupertas. &amp; auitus apto cũ lare fundus.</l>
                <l>Crescit occulto uelut arbor aeuo </l>
                <seg xml:id="seg_Ø_2">Ø</seg>
                <l>Fama marcelli. micat iñt õms</l>
                <note type="addition">l</note>
                <!-- target of gloss is unclear -->
                <l>Iuliũ sidus uelut int̃ ignes luna minores</l>
                <l>Gentis humanȩ pater atq; custos</l>
                <l>Orte saturno. tibi cura magni</l>
                <l>Caesaris fatis data. tu secundo Caesare regnes </l>
                <l>Ille seu parthos latio imminentes </l>
                <note target="#Egerit_1" type="synonym">subegerit</note>
                <l><seg xml:id="seg_Egerit_1">Egerit</seg> iusto domitos triumpho</l>
                <l>Siue subiectos orientis orae Seras &amp; indos.</l>
                <note target="#aequus_1" type="synonym">iustus</note>
                <l>Te minor latũ reg&amp; <seg xml:id="seg_aequus_1">aequus</seg> orbem. Tu graui
                    currũ quaties olympum.</l>
                <l>Tu parũ castis inimica mittes fulmina lucis.</l>
            </ab>
            <!-- end of ode 1,12-->
            <!-- marginal glosses on the right side of the manuscript page -->
            <ab>
                <metamark>S</metamark>
                <note target="#seg_S_1" type="commentary">
                    <p>adhuc romanos duces &amp; nobiles p̃t̃eundo cõmemo rat. ut augustũ
                        p̃ferat cunctis. nã romulus urbis rom̃ȩ ꝯditor ẽ. Num põpiliuꝰ a curib;
                        sabinus ad regnũ uocatꝰ sacroꝵ inuentor ẽ.</p></note>
                <metamark><hi>∵</hi></metamark>
                <note target="#seg_trikolon_2" type="commentary">
                    <p>Tarqͥnus qͦq; rex uirtute magnꝰ. s; hic ꝑⁱscũ posuit ñ suꝑbũ. nã suꝑbos
                        fasces nobiles dix̃.</p></note>
                <metamark><hi>ꝓ</hi></metamark>
                <note target="#seg_ꝓ_1" type="commentary">
                    <p> Cato dũ mortuo põpeio apđ uticã obsideret;. amore lib̃tatis manu sua
                        sese ꝑemit. unđ̃ &amp; uticensis uocatꝰ ẽ.</p></note>
                <metamark><hi>S</hi></metamark>
                <note target="#seg_S_2" type="commentary">
                    <p>Regulũ aut̃ cũ afros uicisset ab hisdẽ cũ ꝑaucis captꝰ ÷. quẽ dũ
                        cartaginenses romã misissent ꝓ cõmutatione captiuoꝵ. adqͥescentes romanos
                        suo ꝯsilio reuocaũ. hunc poeni dũ memoꝵ sacram̃ti reũteret;. sectis
                        palpebris uigiliis necauer̃. </p></note>
                <metamark><hi>SS</hi></metamark>
                <note target="#seg_SS_1" type="commentary">
                    <p>Pauluꝰ ⁊ tirentiuꝰ uarro ꝯsules adũsuꝰ hannibalẽ missi s̃. hi similit̃
                        apd carinas apuliȩ uicũ grandi exercitꝰ romani clade superati s. paulus
                        ̃pteaqũ tantã uitio collegae suoꝵ uidisset stragẽ se ꝑimdũ hoˢtib;
                        dedit</p></note>
                <metamark><hi>SSS</hi></metamark>
                <note target="#seg_SSS_1" type="commentary">
                    <p>Fabriciuˢ qͦq; magnis p̃mus a rege pyrro tẽptatꝰ. dũ nimis pauꝑ censu
                        eˢˢet. corrũpi ñ potuit. de qeqᵒ lucañ. qͦ te fabriciuꝰ regi ñ uendidit
                        auro.</p></note>
                <metamark><hi>c</hi></metamark>
                <note target="#seg_c_1" type="commentary">
                    <p>Curiuꝰ pauꝑtate clarꝰ. de agro ad ꝯsulatũ euocatꝰ ÷ qͥ ñ totondit
                        cesariẽ. ꝓpt̃ ĩuriã ̃pturẽ.</p></note>
                <metamark><hi>u</hi></metamark>
                <note target="#seg_u_1" type="commentary">
                    <p>Camilluꝰ de exilio reũsus. uictores gallos urbe pepulit. &amp; ad
                        intñecionẽ cecidit. uictorꝙ sua sponte in exiliũ rediit</p></note>
            </ab>
            <!-- marginal gloss in lower margin of manuscript page -->
            <ab>
                <metamark>Ø</metamark>
                <note target="#seg_Ø_2" type="commentary">
                    <p>Marcellũ octauie dic̃ filiũ sororis cesaris. qͥ puer mortuuꝰ ÷. de qͦ
                        uirg̃ si q̃ fata aspera rũpas tu marcellũ eris. Aut illũ cõmemorat qͥ
                        pͥmꝰ hannibalẽ apđ nolanã ciuitatẽ ĩ fugã cõpulit. ⁊ ab eo pꝰea
                        occisus est.</p>
                </note>
            </ab>
        </body>
    </text>
